  "body": "Consider the following route config:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    - match:\r\n        prefix: \"/foo\"\r\n      route:\r\n        cluster: \"does_not_exist\"\r\n        request_mirror_policy:\r\n          cluster: \"mirror_cluster_does_exist\"\r\n          runtime_fraction:\r\n            runtime_key: \"mirror_key\"\r\n            default_value:\r\n              numerator: 100\r\n              denominator: \"HUNDRED\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhere the `does_not_exist`destination cluster isn't present. Is the expectation\r\nfor mirroring to still work? It currently doesn't.\r\n\r\nI guess one could argue that, if the destination cluster doesn't exist then the route\r\nis effectively broken and thus mirroring is broken too.\r\n\r\nIf this the case, we can tight up the docs to make that clear. If we still want mirroring\r\nto work, even when the destination cluster is missing, I'll send a PR to handle that.\r\n\r\nThoughts?\r\n\r\ncc: @derekargueta ",
